  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      1. To compare hs-TnT levels after a cardiac stress test in patients with vs. patients
           without CAD

        2. To assess the level of post-exercise hs-TnT predicting CAD (using ROC-analysis)

        3. To determine the sensitivity, specificity and accuracy of this exercise-induced hsTopT
           level in predicting CAD, either alone or in relation to traditional patient-related and
           exercise test-related metrics
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
